<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call passes (struct lfs_mlist*)file to lfs_mlist_isopen which is declared as taking non-const pointers, but lfs_mlist_isopen only inspects the list and does not modify *head or *node. Therefore the parameters (and the argument) could and should be const-qualified (e.g. const struct lfs_mlist *). By using a non-const pointer/cast here the code fails to qualify pointers as const where possible, violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. A fix is to change lfs_mlist_isopen to take const struct lfs_mlist *head, const struct lfs_mlist *node and call it with (const struct lfs_mlist*)file (or avoid the cast if types permit).
</scenario>
